Global Funds Sell Net 1.16 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-04-11T03:31:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/global-funds-sell-net-1-16-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors sold a net 1.16
billion rupees ($26.4 million) of Indian equity  derivatives  on
April 8, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 1 percent to 920.1 billion rupees, or 35.4
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds bought a net 3.85 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment on April 8, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
